OL,3,CCost of new drugs 'do not always
OL,4,Cjustify the benefits', researchers warn
OL,6,FResearchers said that while new drugs
OL,7,F"could have benefited patients who
OL,8,Freceived them" access "came at a
OL,9,Fconsiderable cost for others who might
OL,10,Fhave missed out on potential health
OL,11,Fgains due to necessary disinvestment
OL,12,For underinvestment in other forms of
OL,13,Fcare to fund these newly recommended
OL,14,Fdrugs".
OL,16,FLead author Huseyin Naci, associate
OL,17,Fprofessor of health policy at the LSE,
OL,18,Fadded: "New drugs can be a lifeline
OL,19,Ffor patients who have significant
OL,20,Funmet clinical needs.
