OL,3,CCost of new drugs 'do not always
OL,4,Cjustify the benefits', researchers warn
OL,6,FProf Naci added: "After more than a
OL,7,Fdecade of underinvestment in the NHS,
OL,8,Fit may no longer be justifiable to
OL,9,Fhave a Nice threshold that doesn't
OL,10,Freflect the amount the NHS needs to
OL,11,Fspend to generate health.
OL,13,F"Lowering the threshold would allow
OL,14,Fthe NHS to negotiate better prices for
OL,15,Fnew medicines, taking into account not
OL,16,Fonly the benefits to patients
OL,17,Freceiving these drugs but also the
OL,18,Fimpact on other NHS users who may lose
OL,19,Fout due to resource reallocation."
